  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/6553172/" class="title-link">很有体系的一本教材</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-6553172"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/60160733/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/user_normal.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/60160733/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">文质</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2014-02-18"
      class="main-meta">2014-02-18 16:03:46</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_6553172_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  赵书的最大特点是有一种整体意识。本书介绍的哲学史基本属于传统形而上学，这就决定了哲学家存在一个最基本的逻辑环节，而本书的特点就在于把每个哲学家最基本的逻辑环节讲出，然后把其他的观点按照此逻辑具体的展开。比如说柏拉图的分离，亚里士多德的现实性与潜在性，奥古斯...

                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">3有用 / 0没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
          </div>
